The Directorate of State Service (DSS) in Taraba State has arrested and paraded three suspects with over 300 permanent voters cards (PVCs). The Acting State Director of the DSS, Tunji Bakari, paraded the suspects in Jalingo, the state capital. He said the arrest followed information the police received in collaboration with other security agencies. The PVC, according to the DSS, were recovered in the house of a  special assistant to Governor Darius Ishaku whose  name was withheld. Other items found in the house located at Moyo-gwai area of Jalingo included machetes, bow and arrows and other locally made arms.  Police parade car robbery syndicate in Taraba Police parade ex-DSS operative over kidnapping Gov Ishaku urges Taraba residents to collect their PVCs